                            <h5 style="font-weight: bold;">PRESIDENT APPOINTING MINISTERS</h5>
                            <img class="img-fluid" src="images/Robinah-Nabbanja.jpg" alt="image" style="">
                            <p>
                                Tuesday, the 8th June, 2021 saw H.E The president, by virtue of the authority given to the President of Uganda by Articles: 108(2), 108A(1), 113(1) and 114(1) of the 1995 Constitution of the Republic of Uganda, appoint H.E the Vice President, Rt. Hon. Prime Minister, Honourable Cabinet Ministers and other Ministers.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                As with most of the stories this week, this too gave birth to a very wide and deep discussion across all platforms, social and news media! Major discussions around the appointments of the Vice President and the Prime Minister; both being women!
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                Appointed for the office of the Vice president and the Prime Minister, is Hon. Jessica Alupo and Hon. Robinah Nabbanja, respectively. Women in such high appointment positions are still cited in offices such as 1st Deputy Prime Minister and Minister for East African Community Affairs, to be held by Hon. Rebecca Kadaga.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                Hon. Lukia Nakadama for 3rd Deputy Prime Minister and Minister without Port-folio. Hon. Museveni Janet Kataaha for Minister of Education and Sports. The list goes on and on, seeing H.E the President surrounding himself with the advice of our mothers this time round!
